"security concerns. It will preserve your customizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:193
#: 8c49b8cd3bbd4459868aec43720b23ac
msgid ""
"**Reinstall the template.** This is appropriate for both "
"misconfigurations and security concerns, but you will lose all "
"customizations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:195
#: b147030940c14ff1a60d479a1eb6d009
msgid ""
"**Full revert.** This is appropriate for both misconfigurations and "
"security concerns, and it can preserve your customizations. However, it "
"is a bit more complex."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:198
#: 4cc33ac0905f48ec94f00f8dba530953
msgid "Root revert"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:200
#: 65b85787a98f434ab0af8f44589e6f60
msgid ""
"This command will roll back any changes made *during the last time the "
"template was run, but* **not** *before.* This means that if you have "
"already restarted the template, using this command is unlikely to help, "
"and you’ll likely want to reinstall it from the repository instead. On "
"the other hand, if the template is already broken or compromised, it "
"won’t hurt to try reverting first. Just make sure to **back up** all of "
"your data and changes first!"
msgstr ""

