#: f81b700f082848fe9dde3f9e742b572e
msgid ""
"List the names of the available desktop shortcuts by running the command "
"``ls /usr/share/applications`` and find the exact name of the shortcut to"
" the app you want to autostart:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:345
#: 79e351e1ac054d709ce3aebe7c53afe4
msgid "Create the autostart directory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-install-software.rst:351
#: 20e64dc1f7ce44178696ee9fa1cdc6f2
msgid ""
"Make a link to the desktop app file you’d like to start in the autostart "
"directory. For example, the command below will link the Thunderbird app "
"into the autostart directory:"
